This paper deals with utility-oriented mining, which is a subfield of data mining and database systems. Therefore, cs.DB is the most likely category. The paper also introduces a novel tree structure and pruning strategies, which are related to algorithms and artificial intelligence, respectively, making cs.AI a likely category as well. The paper also proposes an efficient algorithm for mining high-utility patterns, which falls under the category of data mining (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the performance of the algorithm in terms of runtime and memory usage, which are related to machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR), respectively.
